18/03/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The deadline for submitting candidates to run in the April 6th presidential election expired on Monday (March 17th). 
The State Election Commission now has 48 hours to approve the list of candidates. 
Already confirmed are incumbent Filip Vujanovic, Andrija Mandic of the Serb List, Nebojsa Medojevic of the opposition Movement for Changes party, and the leader of the Socialist People's Party, Srdjan Milic. 
(Republika, RTCG - 17/03/08)
